      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "There is no single \"gold standard\" for sophistication that applies universally; the very idea that one set of rules dominates London, Dubai, Singapore, and New York ignores the deep-seated cultural hierarchies and historical power dynamics that define these cities. True global competence is actually about mastering the specific, often rigid, expectations of the dominant cultures in each region rather than adhering to a vague universal baseline. If you are serious about high-level finance and diplomacy, your focus should be on learning the specific, often exclusionary norms of the elite circles in those specific locations, not inventing a fake universal standard.",
